rComments: Mostly positives but work intensive... a bit unnecessary. It's nice to learn things that will be needed later in university, but really, I have yet to be assigned papers as long  in mainstream courses for first and second year, so it was a bit too much for a TYP course.

Very passionate and cares about her students. She will provide the support you need but still has high expectations and challenges you. She likes clear, concise writing. There is a lot of room to choose your own topics for papers, so you can be creative. Very accessible if you need to talk to her outside of class, easy to approach. Great prof!
